         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">4/4/83. ¶  ¶ I am beholden to you, dear Mr Dyer, for your kind sending of fruits of the Alexandrian Senna, ¶  which on behalf of Kew I will send to such cultivators, as likely will take care of the se...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.04.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-90, f. 60.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4/4/83.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am beholden to you, dear Mr Dyer, for your kind sending of fruits of the Alexandrian Senna,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Cassia acutifolia</seg>; see B91.13.10, p. 97.</p>
               </note> which on behalf of Kew I will send to such cultivators, as likely will take care of the seeds and subsequent plants. When Director of the Melb. bot. Garden I raised more than once the principal Sennas; but as at <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">my time</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>no large pumping works were allowed for water supply, for which <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">after</hi>
               </seg> my time £6000 were spent, irrespective of the cost to work the pumps, I could do no good with the plant; the Melbourne night frosts during the short days, when the thermometer will go down occasionally to 24<seg style="">º</seg>F., are also against these Cassias.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I tried therapeutically some of the Australian Cassias, especially those of the C. artimisioides<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>artemisoides?</p>
               </note> group, but found them more drastic then ordinary Sennas.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cassia%20artimisioides">Cassia artimisioides</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
